					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>Idra raba and Idra zuṭa of Sefer ha-zohar.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="183v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Zohar (Idra raba ṿe-Idra zuṭa)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">זהר (אדרא רבא ואדרא זוטא)</title>
							<note>
								<p>Idra raba begins on folio 8r, and Idra zuṭa on folio 81r. </p>
								<p>There are a number of variant readings within the lines of the text, and occasional marginal notes.</p>
								<p>Folio 1-7 and 118-120 contain various Arabic notes (partly incomplete and partly repetitions of each other), mostly relating ot the transmission of gold by one person to another). Among the names appearing in those notes are: Yosef Balkhir, Yosef Gozlan, David Levi Baram, Yeshayah Levi Balnasi.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Zohar_1957"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
